 decisions about their own lives. Literacy, thus, is understood as a key practice of voice and citizenship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aLIteracyzUnited States. 0aLiteracyxEconomic aspects. 0aLiteracyxMexico. 0aLiteracyxUnited States. 0aLiteracyzMexico. 0aMexicansxSocial conditionsxUnited StatesxMexicoxUnited States. 0aMexicansxSocial conditions. 0aMexicanszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Literacy.2bisacsh  aDecolonizing literacy.  aGlobalisation.  aIlliteracy.  aLiteracy education.  aLiteracy policies.  aLiteracy politics.  aLiteracy.  aMexico.  aPostcolonialism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769264140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847692641423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847692641/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK